 Engell, tschechischen, slowakischen und britischen Autorinnen und Autoren - führen von einer Sinnverschiebung im Zuge des Denkens der Technik über Fragen der Bildlichkeit bis zur Analyse konkreter bewegter Bilder.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 4aBild. 4aBildwissenschaft. 4aDigitale Medien. 4aKunstwissenschaft. 4aMedialität. 4aMedienphilosophie. 4aMedientheorie. 4aTechnik. 7aART / Criticism.2bisacsh  aDigital Media.  aFine Arts.  aImage.  aMedia Philosophy.  aMedia Theory.  aTechnology.  aVisual Studies.1 aBeilenhoff, Wolfgang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBystricky, Jiri, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBystřický, Jiří, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEngell, Lorenz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEngell, Lorenz, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHubík, Stanislav, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHörl, Erich, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKrtilova, Katerina, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKrtilová, Kateřina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarcelli, Miroslav, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMersch, Dieter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRoth, Nancy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Backlist eBook Package 2000-2013z978311102523008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Highlight Collection Complete Package 2010-2013z9783110352856oZDB-23-TSO08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Hi